# Project Structure Standards

## Overview
This document defines the standards and guidelines for project structure and organization in the mus project.

## Directory Structure
- Keep all Python code in src/mus/
- Keep all tests in tests/
- Keep all configuration in root directory
- Keep all Docker files in docker/
- Keep all documentation in root directory

## Architecture Guidelines
- Follow hexagonal architecture pattern
- Keep domain logic in domain/
- Keep application logic in application/
- Keep infrastructure code in infrastructure/
- Keep web-related code in infrastructure/web/

## File Organization
- One class per file
- Group related functionality in modules
- Keep file sizes reasonable (< 500 lines)
- Use __init__.py files appropriately
- Keep imports organized and minimal

## Naming Conventions
- Use snake_case for files and directories
- Use PascalCase for classes
- Use snake_case for functions and variables
- Use UPPER_CASE for constants
- Use descriptive names that reflect purpose

## Documentation Standards
- Keep README.md up to date
- Document all public APIs
- Include examples in documentation
- Keep implementation_plan.md current
- Document architectural decisions
